@node "About" "About MegaSF"


About

MegaSF is released into public domain to be used in conjunction with
Xenolink BBS sofware only.. The contents of this archive may be
distibuted by any means as long as the files within remain un-altered
in any way..

MegaSF is a utility that enables files to be selected via an ASL requester
and add them to the online users download list.. It works as a compliment
to MegaRXDL allowing the sysop to quickly find files using a requester,
that are, or are not in Xenolink's filecat then create a list of selected
files in T:, for MegaRXDL to find and send to the user as a normal
download..

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Using MegaSF"


Usage.

Simply put MegaSF anywhere you like and double click on it's Icon. A
simple GUI will appear with a selection of 4 remote nodes you wish to
send files to..  Default is node 1.. Selecting OK will bring up a file
requester for you to choose any file you want so add to the users
download list.. (You must be running MegaRXDL, found in MegaCD archive
or a MegaRXDL archive for this program to be of any use)..

Alternatively you can put the main executable in your path and run it
from the CLI.

@endnode

@node "Otions" "MegaSF Options"


Options.

The GUI has two check boxes.. Checking On Node will make the File
requester appear on the Xenolink node screen of your choice, if it is
not open, the requester will default to workbench screen. Checking Quit
Auto will quit the program quietly after you make your selection of
files from the requester.  Without this box checked, you may continue
selecting more files, or change nodes to send to and select further
files.. The ASL file requester may select multiple files by holding down
the shift key as you select.. MegaSF can be used from the CLI.. Use run
MegaSF if you wish it to detach from the CLI window..

@endnode

